contents:
We have a slider composed of 3 slides, obviously we need to hide the previous button in the first slide and next button in the last slide
Below is the slider in our template, the full structure of the slider were omitted for brevity
&lt;ion-slides #slider &gt;...&lt;/ion-slides&gt; &lt;ion-button&gt; Prev &lt;/ion-button&gt; &lt;ion-button &gt;Next&lt;/ion-button&gt; We use ViewChild to get the functionality of our as following
@ViewChild(&#34;slider&#34;, { static: true }) slider; Inside the class will add a couple of boolean properties called isNextButtonVisible and isPrevButtonVisible
isNextButtonVisible = true; isPrevButtonVisible = false; Let&rsquo;s add a utility function to control the state of those controls, the function is given the slideIndex
@ViewChild(&#34;slider&#34;, { static: true }) slider; isNextButtonVisible = true; isPrevButtonVisible = false; prevOrNextButton(slideIndex: number) { this.isPrevButtonVisible = slideIndex !== 0; this.isNextButtonVisible = slideIndex !== 2; } We will make use of the event slideWillChange()
&lt;ion-slides #slider (ionSlideWillChange)=&#34;slideWillChange()&#34;&gt; ... &lt;/ion-slides&gt; &lt;ion-button&gt; Prev &lt;/ion-button&gt; &lt;ion-button &gt;Next&lt;/ion-button&gt; Inside the slideWillChange() will call prevOrNextButton passing the active slideIndex
isNextButtonVisible = true; isPrevButtonVisible = false; prevOrNextButton(slideIndex: number) { this.isPrevButtonVisible = slideIndex !== 0; this.isNextButtonVisible = slideIndex !== 2; } slideWillChange() { this.slider.getActiveIndex().then((slideIndex) =&gt; { this.prevOrNextButton(slideIndex); }); } Finally let’s change the template a bit to include the condition for hide/show controls
&lt;ion-button *ngIf=&#34;isPrevButtonVisible&#34;&gt; Prev &lt;/ion-button&gt; &lt;ion-button *ngIf=&#34;isPrevButtonVisible&#34;&gt;Next&lt;/ion-button&gt;
